stone, Kent, England":"英国肯特麥德斯同","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"英国英格兰肯特麥德斯同","lifeSummary":"当Sir John Beale于1340年出生在英国肯特麥德斯同时，他的父亲Father John Beale20岁，母亲Alice Wolgate18岁。他与Katherine Smith结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1399年在他的家乡享年59岁。"},"hr":{"1340–1399":"1340.–1399.","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380.","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389.","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340.","1382":"1382","1380":"1380.","2 April 1375":"2. travnja 1375.","1413":"1413","1389":"1389.","1345":"1345","1399":"1399.","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Maidstone, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1340–1399":"1340–1399","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","2 April 1375":"2. dubna 1375","1413":"1413","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1399":"1399","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, Anglie","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, Anglie","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Maidstone, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1340–1399":"1340–1399","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","2 April 1375":"2. april 1375","1413":"1413","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1399":"1399","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1340–1399":"1340–1399","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","2 April 1375":"2 april 1375","1413":"1413","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1399":"1399","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Maidstone, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1340–1399":"1340–1399","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","2 April 1375":"2 April 1375","1413":"1413","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1399":"1399","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Beale","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["either from Middle English <i>bel(e)</i> ‘fair, beautiful’ used as a woman's name, or from a pet form of an Old French, Middle English female personal name ending in <i>-bel</i>, especially   Isabel  .","nickname from Middle English <i>bel(e)</i> ‘fair, beautiful’ (Old French <i>bele</i>).","variant of   Beal   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Beales","meanings":["English: variant of   Beale  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Isabel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Alfonso, Alvarado, Augusto, Belia, Josefina, Juan, Manuel, Mario, Romero, Santa.","French, Spanish, Portuguese, and English (of French origin): from the Old French female personal name <i>Isabel</i>, which is first recorded in late 11th-century Paris and Maine (France). It was an alternative form of   Elizabeth  , Old French <i>Elisabet</i>, which had a shortened pet form <i>Isabet</i>. <i>Isabel</i> appears to have originated as a variant of <i>Isabet</i>, in which the suffix <i>-el</i> was substituted for <i>-et</i> through re-interpretation of <i>-et</i> as a hypocoristic diminutive. The resultant <i>-bel</i> was early associated with Old French <i>bel</i> ‘fair, beautiful’, as is evident in the French variant <i>Isabeau</i>. From France the name was taken to England, where it achieved considerable popularity in the late medieval period as an independent personal name alongside its rarer doublet <i>Elizabeth</i>. In the form <i>Isabel</i> it also appears in Spain and Portugal, while in Italy it took the form   Isabella  . The French surnames <i>Isabel</i> and   Isabelle   are particularly associated with Normandy.","History: Michel Isabel from Reux in Calvados, France, married Marie Jobidon in Château-Richer, QC, in 1673."]},{"name":"Beal","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Beale  , from Old French <i>bel(e)</i> ‘fair, lovely’ (see   Beau  ), either a nickname for a handsome man or a metronymic from this word used as a female personal name.","English (northern): habitational name from any of the places so named in Northumberland and Yorkshire. The former of these (<i>Behil</i> in early records) is named with Old English <i>bēo</i> ‘bee’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’; the latter (<i>Begale</i> in Domesday Book) with Old English <i>bēag</i> ‘ring’, here probably used in the sense ‘river bend’, or an unattested personal name <i>Bēaga</i> derived from this word + <i>halh</i> ‘nook, recess’ (see   Beagle   2). An additional source may be Beald, a farm in Cambridgeshire, recorded as <i>Bele super Dedhil</i>, <i>c.</i> 1195. In Lincolnshire, the surname is perhaps from a word or name for a farm derived from Scandinavian <i>bøli</i> ‘farm’.","French (<b>Béal</b>): topographic name for someone who lived by a mill race, from the Lyonnaise dialect term <i>béal</i>, <i>bezale</i>, <i>bedale</i> (of Gaulish origin)."]},{"name":"Beals","meanings":["English: variant of   Beale  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":42,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir John Beale was born in 1340, in Maidstone, Kent, England, his father, Father John Beale, was 20 and his mother, Alice Wolgate, was 18. He married Katherine Smith. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1399, in his hometown, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1340–1399":"1340–1399","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","2 April 1375":"2. aprill 1375","1413":"1413","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1399":"1399","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429","Glassenbury, Kent, England":"Glassenbury, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England":"Maidstone, Kent, England","Maidstone, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Maidstone, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1340–1399":"1340–1399","1345–1429":"1345–1429","1355–1380":"1355–1380","1375–1429":"1375–1429","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1322–1413":"1322–1413","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","2 April 1375":"2. huhtikuuta 1375","1413":"1413","1389":"1389","1345":"1345","1399":"1399","1322":"1322","1355":"1355","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1429":"1429",